        "desc2ind": "Masyarakat Jambi terkenal dengan keterlibatan aktif mereka dalam proses persiapan, yang mencakup pembuatan berbagai hiasan, pakaian adat, serta persiapan tempat perayaan. Upacara kumau sendiri sering kali dimulai dengan doa bersama dan persembahan kepada leluhur. Hal ini mencerminkan keberagaman kepercayaan dan keyakinan yang ada dalam masyarakat Jambi, yang melibatkan unsur-unsur agama dan spiritualitas setempat. Setelah itu, acara dilanjutkan dengan serangkaian pertunjukan seni tradisional, seperti tari-tarian dan musik adat, yang menjadi hiburan bagi para hadirin. Pakaian adat juga memegang peran penting dalam tradisi kumau. Pakaian tersebut biasanya merupakan warisan dari generasi sebelumnya, dengan desain dan motif khas Jambi. Warna-warna cerah dan motif-motif tradisional menjadi ciri khas pakaian adat ini, yang tidak hanya mencerminkan keindahan artistik, tetapi juga memiliki makna filosofis yang dalam. Selain itu, hidangan tradisional juga menjadi bagian tak terpisahkan dari tradisi kumau. Masyarakat Jambi cenderung menyajikan makanan khas daerah, seperti rendang Jambi, ketan serundeng, atau berbagai hidangan lain yang merupakan kuliner lokal. Hidangan-hidangan ini tidak hanya memuaskan selera, tetapi juga menjadi simbol kedermawanan dan keberlimpahan dalam tradisi kumau. Tradisi kumau bukan hanya sekadar perayaan, tetapi juga menjadi ajang untuk mempererat ikatan sosial antarwarga. Dalam suasana penuh keakraban, masyarakat saling berbagi cerita, pengalaman, dan kebahagiaan. Hal ini menciptakan atmosfer positif dan memperkuat solidaritas dalam masyarakat. Dengan demikian, tradisi kumau dari Jambi bukan hanya sekedar warisan budaya, tetapi juga merupakan cerminan nilai-nilai kehidupan masyarakat Jambi yang kaya akan kebersamaan, kepercayaan, dan keharmonisan. Perayaan ini tidak hanya memperkaya warisan budaya Indonesia, tetapi juga menggambarkan kekayaan dan keunikannya sebagai bagian dari keberagaman budaya di seluruh dunia.",
        "desc1eng": "The Kumau tradition is a cultural heritage originating from Jambi, a province located on the island of Sumatra, Indonesia. This tradition is a crucial part of the identity of the Jambi community and reflects the cultural richness passed down from generation to generation. In its development, the Kumau tradition has become a symbol of togetherness, trust, and harmony among community members. Kumau itself is a term in the Jambi language that refers to a traditional ceremony or community event. This tradition has deep roots in the daily lives of the Jambi community, and its celebrations are often associated with important moments in the life cycle, such as weddings, births, or even harvest seasons. It is essential to note that the Kumau tradition is not only a formal event but also an expression of camaraderie and community unity. The Jambi community tends to involve the entire village or community in organizing this tradition, creating a lively and joyful atmosphere. One significant moment in the Kumau tradition is the preparation and implementation of the traditional ceremony.",
        "desc2eng": "The Jambi community is known for their active involvement in the preparation process, which includes the creation of various decorations, traditional costumes, and the preparation of the celebration venue. The Kumau ceremony often begins with a communal prayer and offerings to the ancestors, reflecting the diversity of beliefs and spirituality in the Jambi community, involving elements of religion and local spirituality. Afterward, the event continues with a series of traditional art performances, such as dances and traditional music, providing entertainment for the attendees. Traditional costumes also play a significant role in the Kumau tradition. The costumes worn by the dancers usually reference local traditions, featuring bright colors and distinctive ornaments. Each costume element has a specific meaning and function, adding beauty and authenticity to the dance. The Kumau dance movements can be divided into several stages, meticulously arranged to create harmony and coherence. These steps not only showcase the technical skills of the dancers but also convey emotions and stories that deeply engage the audience. The movements may include facial expressions, body positions, and unique hand gestures. The role of Kumau dance in the daily life of the Jambi community is significant. Besides being part of traditional ceremonies, this dance is also present in various cultural celebrations, such as weddings, welcoming important guests, or local festivals. Kumau dance is not only a marker of cultural identity but also a means to preserve and pass down ancestral heritage. Thus, Kumau dance is not just a dance but a living cultural heritage. Amidst modernization, it is crucial for the Jambi community to preserve and celebrate the beauty and meaning encapsulated in the Kumau tradition. This legacy is not only a relic of the past but also an inspiration for future generations to maintain their cultural richness. Through preservation efforts, this dance can remain a distinctive and prideful symbol, bringing the harmony and uniqueness of Jambi's culture to the national and international levels. Increased appreciation from the local community and support from the government are vital in maintaining the sustainability of this tradition.",
