        "desc1eng": "Jugit Dance is one of the traditional dances originating from North Kalimantan, Indonesia. This dance has distinctive features and profound meanings in the local culture. With elegant movements and unique music, Jugit Dance is an integral part of the cultural heritage of North Kalimantan. Jugit Dance is usually performed in various cultural events such as traditional celebrations, customary ceremonies, or art festivals. The name Jugit itself comes from the local language, meaning circular and beautiful movements. The dance reflects the beauty of nature and the daily life of the people of North Kalimantan. Jugit Dance involves graceful and subtle body movements, with a harmonious combination of hand, foot, and body movements. The dancers wear traditional costumes that reinforce the cultural identity of North Kalimantan. These costumes are often adorned with traditional motifs reflecting the richness of artistic and cultural heritage. The music accompanying Jugit Dance typically consists of traditional North Kalimantan instruments such as drums, gongs, flutes, and other percussion instruments. The musical accompaniment provides a unique atmosphere and supports the expressive movements of the dancers.",
