        "desc2ind": "Selama upacara, penari-penari tradisional menggambarkan gerakan-gerakan yang mengandung makna tertentu, mewakili cerita-cerita lama atau mitos yang turun-temurun. Salah satu ciri khas dari Kariaa Lambe adalah penggunaan berbagai alat musik tradisional seperti gong, kulintang, dan kendang. Alunan musik ini tidak hanya mengiringi tarian, tetapi juga dianggap sebagai sarana komunikasi spiritual dengan alam dan leluhur. Musik dan tarian dalam tradisi ini menciptakan suasana yang penuh semangat, merayakan kehidupan dan kebersamaan. Upacara Kariaa Lambe sering kali melibatkan pemberian sesajen atau persembahan kepada roh leluhur. Ini merupakan ungkapan rasa syukur dan penghormatan terhadap warisan budaya yang diteruskan dari generasi ke generasi. Beberapa sesajen mungkin terdiri dari hasil bumi setempat, simbolisasi keseimbangan alam, dan perlambangan keberlanjutan hidup. Tradisi ini juga menjadi kesempatan bagi masyarakat untuk memperkuat hubungan sosial. Setelah selesai upacara, seringkali diadakan acara pesta rakyat yang melibatkan seluruh komunitas. Ini menciptakan kesempatan bagi orang-orang untuk berbagi cerita, pengalaman, dan mempererat ikatan emosional di antara mereka. Dalam beberapa tahun terakhir, Kariaa Lambe juga menjadi daya tarik wisata. Banyak wisatawan yang tertarik untuk menyaksikan keindahan dan kekayaan budaya Sulawesi Tenggara melalui partisipasi dalam upacara ini. Namun, perlu diingat bahwa partisipasi wisatawan harus dilakukan dengan rasa hormat dan kesadaran terhadap nilai-nilai budaya setempat. Kariaa Lambe perlu dijaga dan dilestarikan agar dapat terus diwariskan kepada generasi mendatang. Pemerintah, lembaga budaya, dan masyarakat lokal dapat bekerja sama dalam upaya pelestarian ini, termasuk dengan mendokumentasikan dan mempromosikan tradisi ini baik di tingkat nasional maupun internasional. Dengan demikian, Kariaa Lambe dapat terus berkembang dan memberikan kontribusi positif bagi identitas budaya Sulawesi Tenggara.",
        "desc1eng": "The Kariaa Lambe tradition is a traditional ceremony originating from Southeast Sulawesi, Indonesia. This ceremony holds deep historical, cultural, and spiritual significance for the local community. In this tradition, various elements reflect the local wisdom and cultural richness of Southeast Sulawesi. Kariaa Lambe is generally performed to celebrate significant moments in the lives of the people of Southeast Sulawesi, such as weddings, births, or even deaths. Essentially, this tradition aims to strengthen social bonds, honor ancestors, and express gratitude to nature and supporting spirits. An important aspect of Kariaa Lambe is the community-wide preparation. People come together to prepare everything, from physical arrangements to spiritual preparations. This collaborative effort creates a climate of cooperation and interdependence among community members. The ceremony begins with a series of traditional rituals, including sacred prayers and traditional songs with sacred meanings. The costumes worn in Kariaa Lambe also hold high symbolic value, often reflecting the richness of local heritage and the history of the community.",
        "desc2eng": "During the ceremony, traditional dancers depict movements that carry specific meanings, representing ancient stories or inherited myths. One distinctive feature of Kariaa Lambe is the use of various traditional musical instruments such as gongs, kulintang, and kendang. This energetic and rhythmic music serves not only as an accompaniment to the dance but is also considered a means of spiritual communication with nature and ancestors. The music and dance in this tradition create a spirited atmosphere, celebrating life and togetherness. Kariaa Lambe ceremonies often involve the offering of ritualistic items or presentations to ancestral spirits. This is an expression of gratitude and respect for the cultural heritage passed down from generation to generation. Some offerings may consist of local produce, symbolizing the balance of nature and the symbolism of the continuity of life. This tradition also provides an opportunity for the community to strengthen social relationships. After the ceremony, community-wide festivities are often held, creating opportunities for people to share stories, experiences, and strengthen emotional bonds among them. In recent years, Kariaa Lambe has also become a tourist attraction. Many visitors are interested in witnessing the beauty and cultural richness of Southeast Sulawesi by participating in this ceremony. However, it is essential to remember that tourist participation should be done with respect and awareness of local cultural values. Kariaa Lambe needs to be preserved and maintained to be passed on to future generations. Government authorities, cultural institutions, and local communities can collaborate to document and promote this tradition nationally and internationally. Thus, Kariaa Lambe can continue to evolve and positively contribute to the cultural identity of Southeast Sulawesi.",
